	<paragraphs xml:id="parameters">
	<title>Parameters</title><p/>

		<!-- %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% -->
		<!-- %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% -->

		<p>
			At the top of the script is a list of parameters. These parameters are constant values that control different factors in the simulation.  Each parameter has an initial value, but these can be adjusted. You will need to use the parameters as input values for your functions. That way if you choose to change the values of some parameters, you only need to change its value in one line of the script. Table <xref ref="param"/> summarizes the parameters.
		</p>

		<table xml:id="param">
			<title>Parameters for the fire spreading simulation.</title>
			<tabular halign="center">
				<row bottom="minor">
					<cell>Parameter</cell>
					<cell left="minor">Description</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>T</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Max number of time steps in simulation</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>N</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Number of grid spaces in each direction of the forest</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>probTree</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Probability that a tree is in a space initially</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>probBurn</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Probability that a tree is initially burning</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>probGrowth</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Probability that a tree grows in an empty space</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>probParty</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Probability that a party starts another fire</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>probCatch</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Probability that tree catches fire from its neighbor</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>burnTime</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Timesteps until a burning space becomes empty</cell>

				</row>
			</tabular>
		</table>
		<!-- %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% -->
		<!-- %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% -->
	</paragraphs>

	<paragraphs xml:id="model-variables">
	<title>Variables</title><p/>

		<!-- %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% -->
		<!-- %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% -->
		  Information about the <c>N</c><m>\times</m><c>N</c> forest is stored in a variable called Forest. Forest is an <c>N</c><m>\times</m><c>N</c> matrix of the
		 form where each space is classified as Empty (stored as a 0), Tree (stored as a 1), or Burning (stored as an integer larger or equal to 2). We want to track how long a space has been burning. We will use 2 to represent a space that just started burning, 3 to represent a space that has been burning for 2 timesteps, and in general <c>j</c>+1 to represent a space that has been burning for <c>j</c>  timesteps.

		<p>
			We also want to track the number of spaces that are empty, trees and burning at each time step. Empty, Tree, and Burning are each a vector of length <c>T</c>. Lastly, the counter variable just counts the number of time steps taken in the simulation. Table <xref ref="var"/> summarizes the variables.
		</p>


		<table xml:id="var">
			<title>Variables for the fire spreading simulation.</title>
			<tabular halign="center">
				<row bottom="minor">
					<cell>Variable</cell>
					<cell left="minor">Description</cell>
					<cell>Size</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>Forest</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Current status of each space in the forest</cell>
					<cell><c>N</c><m>\times</m><c>N</c></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>Empty</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Number of empty spaces at each time step</cell>
					<cell><c>T</c><m>\times</m><c>1</c></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>Tree</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Number of tree spaces at each time step</cell>
					<cell><c>T</c><m>\times</m><c>1</c></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>Burning</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Number of burning spaces at each time step</cell>
					<cell><c>T</c><m>\times</m><c>1</c></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><c>counter</c></cell>
					<cell left="minor" halign="left">Number of time steps taken in the simulation</cell>
					<cell><c>1</c><m>\times</m><c>1</c></cell>
				</row>
			</tabular>
		</table>
	</paragraphs>


</section>